cs.HCI, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.DL 

The paper proposes a data structure and visualization interface for analyzing the fine-grained history of document writing. This involves processing and analyzing large amounts of data, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HCI). Additionally, the paper discusses natural language processing techniques for analyzing the text, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the hierarchical structure of the final text, which could fall under cybernetics (cs.CY) or deep learning (cs.DL) if machine learning techniques were used to analyze the structure.
